ZH: 清洁工每天都要保持办公室的整洁。
EN: The janitor has to keep the office clean every day.

ZH: 昨天清洁工擦了窗户，现在整个房间都亮了起來。
EN: The janitor cleaned the windows yesterday, and now the whole room looks brighter.

ZH: 清洁工把垃圾桶里的垃圾都清理干净了。
EN: The janitor cleaned out all the trash from the garbage can.

ZH: 公园里的清洁工每天都要清扫地面上的落叶。
EN: The janitors in the park have to sweep up the fallen leaves every day.

ZH: 这座大楼的清洁工是个很负责任的人。
EN: The janitor in this building is a very responsible person.

ZH: 清洁工用拖把擦地板的时候一定要注意安全。
EN: The janitor must pay attention to safety when mopping the floor.

ZH: 他是这家公司的清洁工，负责所有办公区域的清洁工作。
EN: He is the janitor of this company, responsible for cleaning all office areas.

ZH: 清洁工的工作艰苦却也很重要。
EN: The janitor's job is tough but very important.

ZH: 每个人都应该尊重清洁工的工作。
EN: Everyone should respect the work of the janitor.

ZH: 清洁工曾经在这所学校工作了十年。
EN: The janitor worked at this school for ten years.

ZH: 清洁工正在清扫地板，所以请不要踩进去。
EN: The janitor is mopping the floor, so please do not step on it.

ZH: 如果你是个清洁工，你会怎么处理这个问题？
EN: How would you handle this issue if you were a janitor?

ZH: 清洁工点亮了所有的灯，让整个走廊变得更明亮。
EN: The janitor turned on all the lights, making the whole hallway brighter.

ZH: 这家公司的清洁工是个优秀的员工。
EN: The janitor in this company is an outstanding employee.

ZH: 清洁工每周会清理一次窗户。
EN: The janitor cleans the windows once a week.

ZH: 这所学校的清洁工很快就把垃圾桶清空了。
EN: The janitor at this school quickly emptied the trash cans.

ZH: 我妈妈以前是个清洁工，她说那是一项很辛苦的工作。
EN: My mom used to be a janitor, and she said it was a hard job.

ZH: 清洁工不只是擦地板，他们还要负责打扫厕所和清洁工具。
EN: Janitors don't just mop floors, they also have to clean toilets and tools.

ZH: 清洁工正在修理故障的扫地机器人。
EN: The janitor is repairing the malfunctioning floor-cleaning robot.

ZH: 如果你有机会，一定要感谢一下这个楼里的帮手——清洁工。
EN: If you have the chance, be sure to thank the helper in this building - the janitor.
